<p>I am unziping a file using java. </p>  <p>Long ago, somewhere I've got this class in the internet, and I stole and kept it for my own usage. The complete class is:</p>  <pre><code>package pubapp.data;  import java.io.BufferedOutputStream; import java.io.File; import java.io.FileInputStream; import java.io.FileOutputStream; import java.io.IOException; import java.util.zip.ZipEntry; import java.util.zip.ZipInputStream;   public class UnzipUtility {     private static final int BUFFER_SIZE = 4096;      public void unzip(String zipFilePath, String destDirectory) throws IOException {         File destDir = new File(destDirectory);         if (!destDir.exists()) {             destDir.mkdir();         }         ZipInputStream zipIn = new ZipInputStream(new FileInputStream(zipFilePath));         ZipEntry entry = zipIn.getNextEntry();         // iterates over entries in the zip file         while (entry != null) {             String filePath = destDirectory + File.separator + entry.getName();             if (!entry.isDirectory()) {                 // if the entry is a file, extracts it                 extractFile(zipIn, filePath);             } else {                 // if the entry is a directory, make the directory                 File dir = new File(filePath);                 dir.mkdir();             }             zipIn.closeEntry();             entry = zipIn.getNextEntry();         }         zipIn.close();     }  private void extractFile(ZipInputStream zipIn, String filePath) throws IOException {             try (BufferedOutputStream bos = new BufferedOutputStream(new FileOutputStream(filePath))) {                 byte[] bytesIn = new byte[BUFFER_SIZE];                 int read = 0;                 while ((read = zipIn.read(bytesIn)) != -1) {                     bos.write(bytesIn, 0, read);                 }             }         }     } </code></pre>  <p>This works in my local computer <code>(windows 7, jdk_1.7, tomcat)</code> fine. But when I upload war to remote hosting, it does no work as expected. It does not create the sub directories. Web hosting is using Debian/Ubuntu, jdk_1.7, tomcat-7.x</p>  <p>What is wrong with this code in linux?</p>